From: Dragos-Bogdan Chirila <dchirila@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] xwayland: guard seatless pointer-warp against a NULL wl_seat

xwl_cursor_warped_to() dereferences xwl_seat->focus_window without first
checking that the seat is non-NULL. When the Wayland compositor advertises
no wl_seat (for example Weston's headless backend, which vkrelay2 uses and
drives application input out-of-band through XTEST), xwl_screen_get_default_seat()
returns NULL and any client pointer warp -- e.g. an application recentering
the pointer during a view rotation -- crashes Xwayland with a NULL dereference
at &((struct xwl_seat *)0)->focus_window (offset 0xa0 on this ABI).

The sibling callback xwl_cursor_confined_to() already guards this exact
condition with `if (!xwl_seat) return;`. Mirror that guard here: with no
wl_seat there is no Wayland pointer whose position could be emulated, so
returning without emulation is the correct behaviour. The X server's core
warp has already happened; this callback is only the Wayland-side emulation
hook.

Reproduced deterministically by vkrelay2-rotate-canary (a pure-xcb client
that grabs the pointer and XWarpPointer-recenters) on a seatless
weston-headless + rootless-Xwayland stack; the same guarded build survives it.

--- a/hw/xwayland/xwayland-screen.c
+++ b/hw/xwayland/xwayland-screen.c
@@ -229,6 +229,14 @@
     if (!xwl_seat)
         xwl_seat = xwl_screen_get_default_seat(xwl_screen);
 
+    /* A seatless compositor (for example Weston's headless backend, which
+     * advertises no wl_seat) leaves xwl_screen_get_default_seat() returning
+     * NULL. There is then no Wayland pointer whose position we could emulate,
+     * so mirror the guard already present in xwl_cursor_confined_to() and bail
+     * out instead of dereferencing a NULL seat in the focus_window test below. */
+    if (!xwl_seat)
+        return;
+
     if (!window)
         window = XYToWindow(sprite, x, y);
 
